1
00:00:01,209 --> 00:00:02,335
[JAO VOICEOVER] Magic.

2
00:00:03,169 --> 00:00:05,338
We’re all looking for magic.

3
00:00:05,630 --> 00:00:06,715
In places,

4
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:08,800
in our lives,

5
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:10,719
and even in love.

6
00:00:11,052 --> 00:00:12,887
Especially in love.

7
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:14,556
But,

8
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:17,183
is love still worth fighting for

9
00:00:17,225 --> 00:00:19,227
when the magic is gone?

10
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:21,938
[KARA VOICEOVER] You call it magic.

11
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:23,106
Or mystery.

12
00:00:23,148 --> 00:00:24,815
Because it’s something so deep

13
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:26,401
words can’t describe it.

14
00:00:26,693 --> 00:00:29,154
But every part of your being feels it.

15
00:00:29,779 --> 00:00:32,031
Some people even call it love.

16
00:00:32,741 --> 00:00:34,491
But on this beautiful island,

17
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:37,203
we call it the Siargao Curse.

18
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:44,210
The Siargao Curse has two versions.

19
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:45,879
Curse Number One,

20
00:00:46,087 --> 00:00:49,465
the island makes someone want to stay longer

21
00:00:49,466 --> 00:00:51,593
the moment they set foot in Siargao.

22
00:00:52,177 --> 00:00:55,305
It starts by extending your vacation for a few days.

23
00:00:55,472 --> 00:00:57,140
Exploring the whole island,

24
00:00:57,182 --> 00:00:59,017
befriending the locals,

25
00:00:59,058 --> 00:01:00,435
gazing at the sky,

26
00:01:00,518 --> 00:01:02,187
go surfing, and then…

27
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:04,022
you breathe.

28
00:01:04,063 --> 00:01:06,065
You breathe a deep breath.

29
00:01:06,649 --> 00:01:08,066
At some point, you realize

30
00:01:08,067 --> 00:01:09,778
how happy you’ve been lately.

31
00:01:09,819 --> 00:01:11,571
And then before you know it,

32
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:14,324
you don’t want to leave.

33
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:16,075
You can’t go back home...

34
00:01:16,701 --> 00:01:18,328
because you’re already home.

35
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:22,207
I’m a happy victim of Siargao Curse Number One.

36
00:01:22,874 --> 00:01:24,667
But out of everyone who was cursed,

37
00:01:25,627 --> 00:01:26,795
I'm lucky.

38
00:01:27,545 --> 00:01:30,548
[JAO VOICEOVER] Not everyone gets to experience true love.

39
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:32,884
The kind that exceeds fantasy.

40
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:34,928
Because when you're no longer in love

41
00:01:34,969 --> 00:01:36,930
with each other’s magical version,

42
00:01:37,514 --> 00:01:40,308
real love begins.

43
00:01:40,809 --> 00:01:43,978
Real love takes hard work.

44
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:46,314
But I’m a hard worker.

45
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:49,442
That's why I will fight for our relationship.

46
00:01:49,692 --> 00:01:52,654
They've been saying there's a Siargao Curse Number Two-

47
00:01:52,862 --> 00:01:55,198
it's when your partner breaks up with you

48
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,449
the moment they arrive in Siargao?

49
00:01:57,033 --> 00:01:58,159
I'm not worried.

50
00:01:58,576 --> 00:01:59,869
This is not the curse.

51
00:02:00,328 --> 00:02:01,663
I'm not a victim.

52
00:02:02,372 --> 00:02:03,623
I will find her.

53
00:02:03,873 --> 00:02:05,500
We’ll get back together.

54
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:07,252
As always.

55
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:09,045
What Siargao Curse Number Two?

56
00:02:10,129 --> 00:02:11,548
Every curse has an antidote.

57
00:02:12,131 --> 00:02:16,094
[ALON BY JL]

58
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:28,791
Miss, where can I get a ride going to General Luna?

59
00:03:28,917 --> 00:03:30,543
Just right outside, sir.

60
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:33,546
The white vans head towards GL.

61
00:03:33,796 --> 00:03:37,215
It just takes 30 to 45 minutes from here.

62
00:03:37,216 --> 00:03:39,552
It costs 300 Pesos per person.

63
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:40,136
Okay.

64
00:03:40,178 --> 00:03:42,764
- Welcome to Siargao, Sir…? - Jao.

65
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:44,097
Jao?

66
00:03:44,098 --> 00:03:45,974
As in “very good”?

67
00:03:45,975 --> 00:03:48,811
[SIARGAONON] I hope you enjoy our island, sir!

68
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:50,980
- Thank you! - No problem!

69
00:03:57,612 --> 00:03:58,655
I got this.

70
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:05,828
- Thank you. - You’re welcome.

71
00:04:17,548 --> 00:04:19,801
[RINGING]

72
00:04:21,386 --> 00:04:23,346
[BUSY TONE]

73
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:27,100
Jao, it’s not working anymore.

74
00:04:27,141 --> 00:04:30,645
I’m done. Please don’t look for me.

75
00:04:31,187 --> 00:04:31,980
[JAO VOICEOVER] Babe,

76
00:04:32,021 --> 00:04:33,314
you’ve been ignoring me for five weeks.

77
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:34,774
Let’s fix this.

78
00:04:35,441 --> 00:04:36,943
Babe, I know you miss me.

79
00:04:36,985 --> 00:04:38,194
I miss you, too.

80
00:04:38,444 --> 00:04:39,737
Come home, baby.

81
00:04:40,738 --> 00:04:42,948
Babe, I’m in Siargao. Looking for you!

82
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:43,949
Please talk to me.

83
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:45,827
I have something important to tell you.

84
00:04:47,996 --> 00:04:49,998
Babe, I’m playing your game.

85
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:51,916
Just cooperate with me.

86
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:53,793
Are you from Manila?

87
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:55,877
Yes, ma’am.

88
00:04:55,878 --> 00:04:57,213
Where in Manila?

89
00:04:57,755 --> 00:04:58,840
Makati.

90
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:01,050
Is it your first time in Siargao?

91
00:05:02,927 --> 00:05:05,053
- Where are you from? - Here.

92
00:05:05,054 --> 00:05:08,057
But I worked 25 years in Dubai as an OFW.

93
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:11,101
Are you taking time off?

94
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:13,396
No, I'm staying home here in Siargao.

95
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,480
You must have missed it, huh?

96
00:05:15,481 --> 00:05:16,315
Yes.

97
00:05:16,607 --> 00:05:19,652
My foreign friends in Dubai used to say-

98
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:21,320
“There’s no place like home.”

99
00:05:26,075 --> 00:05:27,869
Sir, can I roll down the window?

100
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:28,911
[DRIVER] Go ahead, sir.

101
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:34,917
Thanks.

102
00:05:35,168 --> 00:05:37,128
Nice to get some fresh air, huh?

103
00:05:38,796 --> 00:05:41,090
Yeah. We don’t get this in Manila.

104
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:43,217
I know.

105
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:51,184
- Waves good? - Yeah!

106
00:05:58,566 --> 00:06:00,234
[CAROL CHUCKLING]

107
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:09,786
I’m gonna miss your leaf-collecting hobby.

108
00:06:09,827 --> 00:06:10,953
There you go again.

109
00:06:11,329 --> 00:06:12,830
I’m not leaving Pacifico!

110
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:14,040
Or are you kicking me out?

111
00:06:14,123 --> 00:06:15,957
Then what about

112
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:18,795
the land you’re paying for in Burgos?

113
00:06:25,134 --> 00:06:27,011
Cloud 9! This is your stop.

114
00:06:28,096 --> 00:06:28,971
Excuse me!

115
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:30,848
- Is this a popular spot? - Yes, sir.

116
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:32,641
Even locals hang out here.

117
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:34,393
Then I’ll get off here, too.

118
00:06:34,435 --> 00:06:35,520
I’ll go grab your bag.

119
00:06:43,861 --> 00:06:44,903
Here you go.

120
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:45,905
Thanks.

121
00:06:58,376 --> 00:06:59,919
[CAROL] But aren’t you excited?

122
00:07:00,128 --> 00:07:00,920
Of course.

123
00:07:00,962 --> 00:07:03,297
Excited to pay off all my debt.

124
00:07:04,048 --> 00:07:06,217
But I don't have plans for that land yet.

125
00:07:06,384 --> 00:07:08,386
You know me, I just go with the flow,

126
00:07:08,427 --> 00:07:10,221
ride the waves.

127
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,931
You sure do.

128
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:13,974
But I’m proud of you!

129
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:16,185
I know you really thought it through.

130
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:18,020
You’re not so reckless anymore.

131
00:07:18,062 --> 00:07:19,063
[CAROL LAUGHS]

132
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:19,981
Not anymore?

133
00:07:20,022 --> 00:07:21,524
Was I impulsive?

134
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:24,610
Impulsive, spontaneous,

135
00:07:24,652 --> 00:07:27,655
fickle-minded, you name it!

136
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,114
Good thing you’ve mellowed down!

137
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:30,283
Namaste.

138
00:07:30,908 --> 00:07:32,160
You know how it is.

139
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:34,452
I have life goals now.

140
00:07:34,453 --> 00:07:36,914
Wow!

141
00:07:38,457 --> 00:07:40,667
How mature of you.

142
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:43,461
So many goals, but no boyfriend!

143
00:07:43,462 --> 00:07:45,423
And that is by choice!

144
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,049
Look at you!

145
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:50,845
But anyone would be lucky

146
00:07:51,429 --> 00:07:52,680
to be loved by you.

147
00:07:52,722 --> 00:07:54,723
Besides being pretty,

148
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:57,768
gentle, sweet, smart,

149
00:07:58,186 --> 00:08:00,188
you also love people,

150
00:08:00,229 --> 00:08:03,065
the mangroves, the island.

151
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,318
That's what I like about you.

152
00:08:05,359 --> 00:08:06,694
You tell the truth.

153
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:09,071
Of course!

154
00:08:09,113 --> 00:08:11,115
I’m Miss Pacifico!

155
00:08:11,991 --> 00:08:14,577
Honesty is the best policy.

156
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:16,495
Wait up!

157
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:23,169
[JAO GRUNTS]

158
00:08:36,474 --> 00:08:37,725
Hey, are you lost?

159
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:38,601
You need help?

160
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:41,561
No, no, I’m good, actually.

161
00:08:41,562 --> 00:08:42,730
Can I ask you, miss…

162
00:08:43,314 --> 00:08:44,440
do you know this person?

163
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:47,109
No, sorry. I’m just a tourist here.

164
00:08:47,401 --> 00:08:48,527
Is she a local?

165
00:08:48,903 --> 00:08:50,112
Not really.

166
00:08:50,154 --> 00:08:52,657
Maybe you can ask one of the locals at the tower?

167
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:54,992
All right. Thank you so much.

168
00:09:04,543 --> 00:09:05,795
[JAO] Do you know her?

169
00:09:05,836 --> 00:09:09,298
- No. - Haven’t seen her here.

170
00:09:09,924 --> 00:09:12,343
Peak season, lots of tourists.

171
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:13,678
She’ll be hard to find.

172
00:09:14,512 --> 00:09:16,472
Where do tourists usually stay here?

173
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:18,598
All over.

174
00:09:18,599 --> 00:09:24,813
Plenty of resorts on Tourism Road and Back Road.

175
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:28,566
You’ve got cheap and expensive options.

176
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:33,531
Malinao has some high end luxury resorts

177
00:09:33,572 --> 00:09:36,325
Maybe you’ll find her there.

178
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:39,787
- Okay, thanks. - Sure.

179
00:10:06,939 --> 00:10:08,941
Look, a heart-shaped cloud.

180
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:11,861
It's really the shape of the clouds that you notice?

181
00:10:12,361 --> 00:10:16,073
Most tourists admire the waves.

182
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:17,450
You’re different.

183
00:11:03,412 --> 00:11:04,662
- Here. - Thank you, sir.

184
00:11:04,663 --> 00:11:06,165
- Keep the change. - Thanks, sir.

185
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:29,730
[HAN BIN] Hello!

186
00:11:29,772 --> 00:11:30,689
Hello.

187
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:32,900
[SIARGAONON] Good morning!

188
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:35,151
- Filipino? - Yes!

189
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:36,529
You speak Tagalog?

190
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:40,366
Just a little bit of Siargaonon.

191
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:43,619
It’s just that you said you’re Filipino.

192
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:45,495
My passport says I’m Korean,

193
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:48,248
but my heart is very Filipino.

194
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:51,252
I’ve been a workaway volunteer all over Asia.

195
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:53,963
And Siargao is home to me.

196
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:55,673
Good for you.

197
00:11:56,507 --> 00:11:57,842
Actually, I have a favor.

198
00:11:57,883 --> 00:12:00,636
I know it’s quite early, but can I check in?

199
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:02,179
I haven’t gotten any sleep.

200
00:12:02,221 --> 00:12:03,931
I’m just really, really tired.

201
00:12:03,973 --> 00:12:06,809
But if you’d like, I can pay extra.

202
00:12:06,851 --> 00:12:09,145
Oh, then very good nice!

203
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:11,396
So, my name is Han Bin.

204
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:12,856
I co-own this resort.

205
00:12:12,857 --> 00:12:15,150
Hi, I’m Jao. Nice to meet you.

206
00:12:15,151 --> 00:12:16,569
Jao, nice to meet you.

207
00:12:16,902 --> 00:12:18,362
You’re so handsome!

208
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:20,281
Richard!

209
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:23,117
I’ll show you around.

210
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:24,243
Sure.

211
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:26,287
So, how long will you stay here?

212
00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:29,039
Not sure yet.

213
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:30,249
Okay.

214
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:33,752
My resort is a bit small,

215
00:12:33,794 --> 00:12:35,671
but it’s beachfront.

216
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:36,547
See?

217
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:38,382
Isn’t it beautiful?

218
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:44,305
- Yeah. - So good.

219
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:46,515
Let’s go upstairs.

220
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:49,643
You know what,

221
00:12:49,685 --> 00:12:51,687
we are also a tour company.

222
00:12:52,354 --> 00:12:53,272
Later we have a tour.

223
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:55,024
If you want to join, just let me know.

224
00:12:55,649 --> 00:12:58,360
So, is this your first time in Siargao?

225
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:01,070
Oh, unfortunately,

226
00:13:01,071 --> 00:13:02,322
we don’t have laundry here.

227
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:05,367
But there are plenty of laundry shops in GL.

228
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:09,705
This is my favorite spot.

229
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:12,458
Guests love to hang out here.

230
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,212
From here, you can see our kitchen

231
00:13:16,253 --> 00:13:17,838
and the bar area.

232
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:20,799
We serve cocktails from 6 PM onwards.

233
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:22,134
And, actually,

234
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:24,345
we do karaoke nights here.

235
00:13:24,553 --> 00:13:25,513
Do you like singing?

236
00:13:25,554 --> 00:13:27,223
Uh, no. Not really.

237
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:28,724
Oh...

238
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:30,392
Have you tried soju?

239
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:33,187
I offer my guests complimentary soju shots

240
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:34,230
as a welcome drink.

241
00:13:34,563 --> 00:13:35,940
Just one shot! It’s really good.

242
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:36,607
Wait.

243
00:13:42,446 --> 00:13:43,739
Here we go!

244
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:45,866
Cheers!

245
00:13:46,158 --> 00:13:47,284
[SIARGAONON] For happiness!

246
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:53,749
That’s strong.

247
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:55,626
Welcome to Katig Hotel.

248
00:13:56,418 --> 00:13:57,419
Thank you.

249
00:13:57,586 --> 00:14:00,214
Here, it’s “salamat karajaw”.

250
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:02,550
[SIARGAONON] Salamat karajaw.

251
00:14:02,591 --> 00:14:03,384
Right.

252
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:21,026
What is this for?

253
00:14:21,485 --> 00:14:24,071
Someone gave it to me but I can’t use it for dyeing,

254
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:25,948
so I’m giving it to you.

255
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:29,618
Maybe you can give it to…?

256
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:33,705
There you go again!

257
00:14:33,706 --> 00:14:34,873
Stop teasing me!

258
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:40,045
Hey, don’t forget, I’m your boss.

259
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:41,046
I can fire you.

260
00:14:41,505 --> 00:14:44,466
If you fire me, I know all your secrets.

261
00:14:45,134 --> 00:14:46,134
[KOREAN] Museun bimil? What secrets?

262
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:47,303
I don’t have any secrets!

263
00:14:52,308 --> 00:14:53,350
Kara...

264
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:55,351
I don’t have a crush on Pearl.

265
00:14:55,352 --> 00:14:57,104
Who said anything about a crush?

266
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:58,355
[KOREAN] Aigoo! Wow!

267
00:14:58,397 --> 00:14:59,772
[KOREAN] Neo wanjeon michyeotda! You’re totally crazy!

268
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:00,608
Hey.

269
00:15:00,649 --> 00:15:01,734
I understood that.

270
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:03,109
You're the crazy one!

271
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:04,445
You're the real crazy one!

272
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:05,988
Get out before I kick you out!

273
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:08,281
Do your job, crazy!

274
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:09,617
Okay, Sir Han.

275
00:15:09,658 --> 00:15:10,451
Bye!

276
00:15:11,118 --> 00:15:12,286
- Pearl! - Yes!

277
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:13,745
Bring Ariel later, okay?

278
00:15:13,746 --> 00:15:14,496
Del Carmen?

279
00:15:14,538 --> 00:15:16,122
Okay! Bye, Kara!

280
00:15:16,123 --> 00:15:17,416
See you later!

281
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:25,507
[HAN BIN CLEARS HIS THROAT]

282
00:15:25,674 --> 00:15:27,258
- Listen. - Sir Han.

283
00:15:27,259 --> 00:15:29,010
We have a new guest upstairs.

284
00:15:29,011 --> 00:15:31,555
Make sure to offer him lunch when he wakes up.

285
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:33,097
Yes, Sir Han, I got you!

286
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:35,808
- And don’t be always on your phone. - Don’t be always on your phone.

287
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:36,769
- Be attentive– - Okay.

288
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:39,063
Are you mocking me?

289
00:15:39,064 --> 00:15:40,355
No, Sir Han!

290
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:42,733
I’m just showing you that I’m being attentive, okay?

291
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:45,027
Because as a Tourism graduate,

292
00:15:45,152 --> 00:15:47,196
I was trained to always listen, right?

293
00:15:47,237 --> 00:15:48,864
And you always say that to me.

294
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:49,948
Because we need–

295
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:51,659
Five-star reviews!

296
00:15:52,117 --> 00:15:52,868
Of course.

297
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:54,161
But more importantly,

298
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:56,914
we are the face of Siargao, Pearl.

299
00:15:56,955 --> 00:15:57,539
Yes, sir.

300
00:15:57,581 --> 00:15:59,792
And I know how much you love Siargao, okay?

301
00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:03,253
Because it embraced me as though I’m from here.

302
00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:06,674
Okay.

303
00:16:06,715 --> 00:16:08,342
Don’t forget to ask our new guest

304
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:10,844
if he wants to join the Del Carmen tour later, okay?

305
00:16:11,261 --> 00:16:12,096
Yes, sir.

306
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:14,556
Do your job.

307
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:35,035
[PATTY] This is amazing!

308
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:37,079
It’s so peaceful.

309
00:16:37,454 --> 00:16:41,750
[ARIEL] This is why Pearl and I always join Kara on her tours.

310
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:43,919
The walk was worth it.

311
00:16:45,087 --> 00:16:47,381
It’s a lot quieter here compared to GL.

312
00:16:47,798 --> 00:16:50,676
This is Del Carmen’s pride.

313
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:53,429
It’s really beautiful here.

314
00:16:53,804 --> 00:16:55,639
It's even better here at sunrise

315
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:57,391
because you will see some mist...

316
00:16:57,433 --> 00:17:00,018
It’s so magical.

317
00:17:01,770 --> 00:17:05,022
This is one of my most favorite spots in Siargao.

318
00:17:05,023 --> 00:17:06,483
That’s why I volunteer with an NGO

319
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:08,527
that helps protect the mangroves.

320
00:17:09,486 --> 00:17:10,821
When a typhoon hit Siargao,

321
00:17:11,613 --> 00:17:13,866
these mangroves helped protect the island.

322
00:17:13,907 --> 00:17:17,786
They acted as a natural buffer against the strong winds,

323
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:20,330
the strong waves, and storm surges.

324
00:17:20,581 --> 00:17:21,915
But, unfortunately,

325
00:17:21,957 --> 00:17:25,877
not everyone understands how important they are.

326
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:28,047
That’s why some people don’t take care of them.

327
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:32,509
Don’t you miss city life?

328
00:17:32,551 --> 00:17:33,552
Not at all.

329
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:35,596
Wow, that was quick.

330
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:40,434
[SIARGAONON] Marajaw karajaw an kinabuhi dinhi sa Siargao.

331
00:17:41,101 --> 00:17:42,477
What does that mean?

332
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:45,314
It means life is good here in Siargao.

333
00:17:45,856 --> 00:17:47,399
“Marajaw” means good.

334
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:51,319
“Karajaw” intensifies it,

335
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:56,617
like saying “very” or “super.”

336
00:17:56,658 --> 00:17:57,658
Intense.

337
00:17:57,659 --> 00:17:58,619
At maximum level.

338
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:04,416
That’s why I see it everywhere.

339
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:05,250
How do they say it?

340
00:18:05,251 --> 00:18:06,585
[SIARGAONON] "Thank you very much."

341
00:18:06,627 --> 00:18:07,836
Actually, I get it.

342
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:12,758
I get why people fall in love with Siargao.

343
00:18:14,134 --> 00:18:15,719
That’s why I decided to stay.

344
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:19,223
- Seriously? - Yup.

345
00:18:19,264 --> 00:18:20,641
I already cancelled my flight

346
00:18:20,682 --> 00:18:22,725
and I’m staying indefinitely.

347
00:18:22,726 --> 00:18:24,186
- Way to go! - Wow!

348
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:26,646
- What about your job in Manila? - Yeah.

349
00:18:26,647 --> 00:18:27,730
I quit.

350
00:18:27,731 --> 00:18:28,690
Before I came here,

351
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:31,026
I was thinking about doing that anyway, so…

352
00:18:31,068 --> 00:18:34,154
I just love the vibe here.

353
00:18:34,696 --> 00:18:37,032
Don’t you mean the parties?

354
00:18:37,324 --> 00:18:39,951
Yup, the parties, the food crawls,

355
00:18:39,952 --> 00:18:40,993
the run clubs.

356
00:18:40,994 --> 00:18:43,247
Sure, you can find those in Manila too.

357
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:46,040
But it just hits different here.

358
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:48,418
Especially the fresh air,

359
00:18:49,711 --> 00:18:50,921
the beaches,

360
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:52,505
the surfing.

361
00:18:52,506 --> 00:18:56,093
You know, I just love the laidback lifestyle.

362
00:18:57,427 --> 00:18:59,429
- And I have you guys. - Us?

363
00:18:59,471 --> 00:19:01,013
Yeah! I mean,

364
00:19:01,014 --> 00:19:03,809
we’ve only been hanging out for a few days but

365
00:19:03,851 --> 00:19:05,477
it feels like I’ve known you forever.

366
00:19:06,228 --> 00:19:07,938
You even introduced me to your brother.

367
00:19:08,146 --> 00:19:10,691
Us Siargaonons are naturally friendly.

368
00:19:11,066 --> 00:19:11,942
Yeah, I feel like it.

369
00:19:11,943 --> 00:19:14,278
I feel like it’s easier to make friends here

370
00:19:14,444 --> 00:19:15,779
than in Manila.

371
00:19:16,321 --> 00:19:17,489
Just friends?

372
00:19:18,615 --> 00:19:20,783
You can have this.

373
00:19:20,784 --> 00:19:21,493
What’s this?

374
00:19:21,535 --> 00:19:23,035
A welcome gift from Siargao.

375
00:19:23,036 --> 00:19:24,204
Thanks.

376
00:19:24,663 --> 00:19:26,456
“The curse is real!”

377
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:30,460
- Thank you. - You’re welcome.

378
00:19:30,502 --> 00:19:31,587
And you, Kara.

379
00:19:31,962 --> 00:19:34,381
What is it about Siargao that made you stay?

380
00:19:36,508 --> 00:19:39,011
Honestly, I wish I was born here.

381
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:42,096
Life just feels calmer here.

382
00:19:42,097 --> 00:19:44,391
Wasn’t it hard starting over?

383
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:47,477
It’s not about whether it’s hard or easy,

384
00:19:47,519 --> 00:19:49,521
but whether it’s worth it.

385
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:51,857
I feel like doors open

386
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:53,901
when you decide to start over.

387
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:56,194
Words of wisdom.

388
00:19:57,362 --> 00:19:58,739
Can I ask you something?

389
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:00,073
Sorry, if it’s too personal,

390
00:20:00,115 --> 00:20:01,199
you don’t have to answer.

391
00:20:01,241 --> 00:20:02,159
Shoot.

392
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:04,995
Are you running away from something?

393
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:09,416
No.

394
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:11,585
Shall we?

395
00:20:14,379 --> 00:20:15,504
[PEARL] I’ll take your pictures.

396
00:20:15,505 --> 00:20:16,965
[PATTY] So, foam party later?

397
00:20:24,806 --> 00:20:26,391
Party!

398
00:20:56,004 --> 00:20:59,466
[MC] Siargao, are you guys ready for the foam party?

399
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:01,093
[CROWD CHEERS]

400
00:21:01,134 --> 00:21:03,386
DJ Neil, on mix one and two!

401
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:05,013
Play the music, brother!

402
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:10,060
[CROWD CHEERS]

403
00:21:11,645 --> 00:21:16,108
[MC] Six, five, four, three, two...

404
00:21:16,149 --> 00:21:19,027
[CROWD CHEERS]

405
00:21:42,259 --> 00:21:43,801
[KARA VOICEOVER] This is my life.

406
00:21:43,802 --> 00:21:46,596
For someone who’s cursed, I’m actually so lucky.

407
00:21:47,681 --> 00:21:48,765
[JAO VOICEOVER] Magic.

408
00:21:49,266 --> 00:21:51,643
We’re all looking for it.

409
00:21:52,185 --> 00:21:53,436
[KARA VOICEOVER] But every blessing

410
00:21:53,437 --> 00:21:54,813
has its own curse.

411
00:21:55,814 --> 00:21:57,024
[JAO VOICEOVER] But what makes magic

412
00:21:57,065 --> 00:21:58,317
truly magical is that

413
00:21:59,109 --> 00:22:00,861
you don't need to look for it.

414
00:22:01,903 --> 00:22:04,906
It finds you.

415
00:22:05,699 --> 00:22:07,701
[KARA VOICEOVER] Is this how the curse starts?

416
00:22:29,681 --> 00:22:30,599
Boss.

417
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:31,849
[TANTAN] What happened, Sir Handsome?

418
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:33,185
You’re really drunk.

419
00:22:33,310 --> 00:22:34,436
I’ll give you a ride to your hotel.

420
00:22:34,478 --> 00:22:35,896
[JAO] Take me to the after party.

421
00:22:36,063 --> 00:22:37,773
Jonathan. Just call me Tantan.

422
00:22:37,981 --> 00:22:40,275
From now on, we’re best friends.

423
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:41,985
[SIARGAONON] Good morning!

424
00:22:42,027 --> 00:22:44,070
Did you enjoy the foam party last night?

425
00:22:44,071 --> 00:22:44,821
I need your help.

426
00:22:44,822 --> 00:22:47,699
I need you to hire the best tour guide in General Luna.

427
00:22:47,949 --> 00:22:49,242
You know, you’re lucky

428
00:22:49,284 --> 00:22:51,161
because we have the best tour guide

429
00:22:51,203 --> 00:22:52,829
in the entire Siargao.

430
00:22:52,871 --> 00:22:54,956
Jao, she’s here!

431
00:22:54,998 --> 00:22:57,374
The best tour guide in Siargao!

432
00:22:57,375 --> 00:22:58,542
Sir Han Bin!

433
00:22:58,543 --> 00:23:01,003
I don’t want to do this. I don’t want drama!

434
00:23:01,004 --> 00:23:03,256
[HAN BIN] This is not a good way to treat our guest.

435
00:23:03,423 --> 00:23:05,926
[JAO] We’ve been living together for five years now.

436
00:23:06,301 --> 00:23:07,552
Have you been in Siargao long?

437
00:23:07,844 --> 00:23:10,596
Seriously, I don’t need to know all these things.

438
00:23:10,597 --> 00:23:11,515
Fiancée.

439
00:23:11,890 --> 00:23:13,183
Ex-fiancée.
